ts of a transnational and century-long social democratic movement, give direction and continuity to the emergence, development, and contestation of income security policies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aCapitalismxHistory. 0aCapitalism. 0aCorporate statexHistory. 0aIncome maintenance programsxHistory. 0aLabor movementxHistory. 0aPublic welfarexHistory. 0aSocial securityxHistory. 0aSocialismxHistory. 0aWelfare economicsxHistory. 0aWelfare statexHistory. 4aPolitical Science & Political History. 4aSociology & Social Science.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013z978311053615740uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150172176240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501721762423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501721762/original  a978-3-11-053615-7  Cornell University Press Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles